.TH AI-PLAYBOOK-COMPLETION 1 "" "ai-playbook" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ai\-playbook\-completion \- Print or install the zsh completion scripts
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBai\-playbook\fR completion <show|install|uninstall> [\-\-to <dir>] [\-\-force]
.SH DESCRIPTION
completion serves the zsh completion scripts rendered at RUNTIME from the
same command registry this help text comes from, so the installed
completions always match the running binary. Meant for `go install` users —
the release archives and the Homebrew formula already ship/install them.
.PP
completion show
    Print the _ai\-playbook completion script to stdout (pipe it anywhere).
.PP
completion install [\-\-to <dir>] [\-\-force]
    Write _ai\-playbook (covers ai\-playbook and apb) and _ask into <dir>,
    creating it as needed. Default <dir>: $XDG_DATA_HOME/zsh/site\-functions
    (~/.local/share/zsh/site\-functions) — add it to your fpath before
    compinit. Existing files are never overwritten without \-\-force.
.PP
completion uninstall [\-\-to <dir>]
    Remove exactly the files install writes; already\-absent files are
    skipped (idempotent — safe as a package post\-uninstall hook).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-to\fR \fI<dir>\fR
target directory instead of $XDG_DATA_HOME/zsh/site\-functions (install/uninstall)
.TP
\fB\-\-force\fR
overwrite already\-installed completion files (install)
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
ai\-playbook completion show
.fi
.PP
.nf
ai\-playbook completion install
.fi
.PP
.nf
ai\-playbook completion install \-\-to ~/.zsh/completions \-\-force
.fi
.SH "SEE ALSO"
\fBai\-playbook\fR(1)
